      summarize(mean_stay = mean(adr))
    ```

-   Are weekend stay costs more at City Hotel?

    I used the filter and summarize functions built into R to give us a mean of the average daily rate paid by guests whose stays did and did not include a weekend, respectively. We can see that the former, those who did stay over a weekend, paid an average of \$107.60 while those who did not paid an average of \$104.53. While a T-test and comparison against a preset P-value would be needed to determine statistical significance, I can weigh in on practical significance. For me as a college student with limited income and funds, this is a significant difference that could add up over the course of a multi-day stay. However, for someone that is traveling for business and has a company that is paying for their travel, this difference might not even be noticed, let alone considered.

